<subSubSection id="C3411C84A53EFF9E6844BA53C93DF902" lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="143" pageId="43" pageNumber="142" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA53EFF996844BA53C9E9FBB2" blockId="43.[826,955,1030,1051]" box="[826,955,1030,1051]" pageId="43" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA53EFF996844BA53C9E9FBB2" box="[826,955,1030,1051]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="142">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA53EFF996844BA7EC929FA38" blockId="43.[826,1441,1067,1425]" pageId="43" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA53EFF996844BA7EC99CFBE9" box="[826,974,1067,1088]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="142">Male: Head:</emphasis>
Face with facial tubercle, gradually sloping dorsally, more abrupt ventrally, entirely yellow, black/dark brown pilose dorsally and laterally, yellow pilose on medial and ventral sections; gena yellow, dark pilose on genal suture; lunule yellow; holoptic; frontal triangle yellowish orange, black pilose; angle between eyes approximately 90Â°; vertical triangle black, black pilose; ocelli reddish; antenna: only scape remains, which is brown, black pilose; occiput black, silver pollinose, yellowish pilose on ventral two thirds, dark pilose on dorsal third.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA53EFF996844BB9EC9B1F8C6" blockId="43.[826,1441,1483,1903]" pageId="43" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA53EFF996844BB9EC9C0FA49" box="[826,914,1483,1504]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="142">Thorax:</emphasis>
Scutum black, with lateral yellow vitta, mainly yellow pilose with black hairs more abundant on posterior quarter; postpronotum yellow; notopleuron yellow continuing until scutellum, yellow pilose; postalar callus yellow, black pilose; scutellum yellow, black pilose, with subscutellar fringe of black hairs. Pleuron mostly yellow, except katepisternum black with dorsal yellow macula, meron black, katatergum black posteriorly, anepimeron black except dorsomedial portion yellow, entirely yellow pilose; metasternum pilose; calypter yellow with long yellow hairs and short black hairs on margin; plumula yellow; halter yellow; spiracular fringes yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA539FF9E6BEEBE93CA92FEB0" blockId="44.[144,759,198,281]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6BEEBE93CA82FF72" box="[144,208,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Wing:</emphasis>
Wing membrane brownish, entirely microtrichose. Alula microtrichose, broad, broader than cell BM.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA539FF9E6BEEBF14CB25FD85" blockId="44.[144,759,320,556]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6BEEBF14CA98FEFF" box="[144,202,321,342]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Legs:</emphasis>
Procoxa black on basal half, yellow on distal half; profemur and tibia yellow, black pilose; protarsus brown except probasitarsomere yellow basally; meso- and metacoxa black, meso- and metatrochanter dark; mesofemur and tibia yellow; metafemur yellow on basal two thirds, dark brown/black on distal third; metatibia dark brown; meso- and metatarsus dark brown, black pilose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA539FF9E6BEEBC01CBD7FC5E" blockId="44.[144,759,595,1015]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6BEEBC01CB53FDC0" box="[144,257,596,617]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Abdomen:</emphasis>
<figureCitation id="1360538AA539FF9E6A6EBC01CBD3FDC0" box="[272,385,595,618]" captionStart="Figures 39â€“50" captionStartId="16.[144,234,1662,1681]" captionTargetBox="[275,1295,194,1618]" captionTargetId="figure-0@16.[271,1295,194,1631]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figures 39â€“50. 39â€“40, Citrogramma solomonense: 39, dorsal view of male abdomen; 40, dorsal view of female abdomen. 41, Citrogramma hervebazini, dorsal view of female abdomen. 42â€“44, Citrogramma quadricornutum: 42, dorsal view of male abdomen; 43, dorsal view of female abdomen; 44, dorsal view of male scutum and scutellum. 45, Citrogramma fumipenne, dorsal view of male abdomen. 46â€“49. Citrogramma luteifrons: 46, dorsal view of female head; 47, dorsal view of male abdomen; 48, lateral view of male pleuron and head; 49, dorsal view of female abdomen. 50, Citrogramma schlingeri, dorsal view of male head." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406165/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Figure 45</figureCitation>
. Parallel-sided, terga 3 and 4 weakly margined. Dorsum mainly black, black pilose dorsally and laterally except tergum 1 yellow pilose laterally and tergum 2 yellow pilose laterally on anterobasal quarter; tergum 1 black; tergum 2 black with two mesolateral round yellow maculae, extended forward laterally to anterolateral tergal margin (like â€˜golf clubâ€™-shaped spots), yellow lateral margin on anterior quarter; terga 3 and 4 black with broad yellow fascia with anterior margin slightly sinuate; tergum 5 black with broad yellow fascia broadened laterally, lateral margin almost entirely yellow; sterna yellow, black pilose; male genitalia small, as in 
<figureCitation id="1360538AA539FF9E6BEEBDB4CBD3FC5E" box="[144,385,993,1015]" captionStart="Figures 122â€“130" captionStartId="23.[164,254,1587,1606]" captionTargetBox="[330,1278,197,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-0@23.[323,1283,195,1558]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figures 122â€“130. 122â€“123, Citrogramma frederici: 122, frontal view of female head; 123, dorsal view of female abdomen. 124â€“126, Citrogramma notiale species group: 124, lateral view of puparium; 125, dorsal view of puparium; 126, posterior view of posterior breathing tube and spiracular openings (detail). 127, Citrogramma citrinum, left lateral view of male genitalia. 128â€“129, Citrogramma henryi: 128, left lateral view of male genitalia; 129, tergum 9 and surstyli, dorsal view. 130, C. henryi (from Vockeroth, 1969 as C. citrinum): a, left lateral view; b, superior lobe, lateral, outline only; c, sternum 9, superior lobes and aedeagal base, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406179" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406179/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Figures 127 and 130</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA539FF9E6BEEBA4ACB39FB9C" blockId="44.[144,363,1055,1077]" box="[144,363,1055,1077]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6BEEBA4ACABBFB9D" box="[144,233,1055,1076]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Female:</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA539FF9E6BEEBA09C8E0FBD8" blockId="44.[144,690,1116,1138]" box="[144,690,1116,1138]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6BEEBA09CB6FFBD8" box="[144,317,1116,1137]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Length (N = 1):</emphasis>
Body, 
<quantity id="4CA3E2EAA539FF9E6AF0BA09CBA3FBD8" box="[398,497,1116,1137]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.17" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" unit="mm" value="11.7">11.7 mm</quantity>
; wing, 
<quantity id="4CA3E2EAA539FF9E6936BA09C8FFFBD8" box="[584,685,1116,1137]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.04" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" unit="mm" value="10.4">10.4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA539FF9E6BEEBACCC876FB06" blockId="44.[144,548,1177,1199]" box="[144,548,1177,1199]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6BEEBACCCBECFB07" box="[144,446,1177,1198]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Geographical distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F34C0F9FA539FF9E6AB6BACCC872FB06" box="[456,544,1177,1199]" name="Taiwan" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA539FF9E6BEEBA83CB4CFA2C" blockId="44.[144,759,1238,1413]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6BEEBA83CBC5FB42" box="[144,407,1238,1259]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Differential diagnosis:</emphasis>
Species with entire yellow face, anepisternum yellow and anepimeron black. Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E6A54BB41CBE7FA81" baseAuthorityName="de Meijere" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[298,437,1299,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteifrons">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6A54BB41CBE7FA81" box="[298,437,1299,1321]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">C. luteifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which differs by having metafemur yellow on basal two thirds and by the different abdominal pattern and geographical distribution.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA539FF9E6BEEBBF9C814F95D" blockId="44.[144,759,1452,1903]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6BEEBBF9CAA9FA68" box="[144,251,1452,1473]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Remarks:</emphasis>
Matsumura described 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E696CBBF8C8FAFA68" authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1916" box="[530,680,1452,1474]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xanthogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumipenne">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E696CBBF8C8FAFA68" box="[530,680,1452,1474]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">X. fumipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a single male from Horisha, 
<collectingCountry id="F34C0F9FA539FF9E6965BB9EC83DFA48" box="[539,623,1483,1505]" name="Taiwan" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
(Formosa), within his work on the economic 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E696ABBBFC8DBF9A9" box="[532,649,1514,1536]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Syrphidae</taxonomicName>
of 
<collectingCountry id="F34C0F9FA539FF9E69CEBBBFC8A4FA56" box="[688,758,1514,1535]" name="Japan" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA32FEA539FF9E6BE9B85DCBB9F9B7" author="Matsumura S &amp; Adachi J" box="[151,491,1544,1566]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" pagination="1 - 36" refId="ref55529" refString="Matsumura S, Adachi J. 1916. Synopsis of the economic Syrphidae of Japan. Pl. [sic] [= Pt] I. Entomological Magazine Kyoto 2: 1 - 36. pl. 1." type="journal article" year="1916">Matsumura &amp; Adachi, 1916</bibRefCitation>
). This species is here transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E6ACFB872C819F995" box="[433,587,1575,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6ACFB872C819F995" box="[433,587,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Citrogramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on morphological characters (head characters, scutellar fringe, and pilose metasternum). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA32FEA539FF9E693BB831C8A5F9D3" author="Shiraki T" box="[581,759,1636,1658]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" refId="ref56243" refString="Shiraki T. 1930. Die Syrphiden des Japanischen Kaiserreiches mit Berucksichtigung benachbarter Gebiete. Memoirs of the Faculty of Science and Agriculture Taihoku Imperial University 1." type="journal volume" year="1930">Shiraki (1930)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed this species and added more specimens from different localities in 
<collectingCountry id="F34C0F9FA539FF9E6AB6B8F4C84DF91E" box="[456,543,1697,1719]" name="Taiwan" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, such as Karenko, Rakuraku, and Taikan, under the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E69E4B895CA80F95D" authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xanthogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumipenne">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E69E4B895CA80F95D" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">X. fumipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and also described the female.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA539FF9E6BD6B8A8CE3DFDC0" blockId="44.[144,759,1452,1903]" lastBlockId="44.[806,1422,198,1443]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">
Amongst the examined material from the island of 
<collectingCountry id="F34C0F9FA539FF9E6BCDB949CB55F89B" box="[179,263,1820,1842]" name="Taiwan" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
(Formosa), I have found three different species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E6B8EB96ECBD4F8E6" authorityName="Mengual" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Matsumura" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[240,390,1850,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xanthogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumipenne" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6B8EB96ECBD4F8E6" box="[240,390,1850,1872]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">C. fumipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21C2E66A539FF9E6AEEB96FC859F8F9" box="[400,523,1850,1872]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E6969B96EC8C2F8E6" authority="Mengual, 2012" authorityName="Mengual" authorityYear="2012" box="[535,656,1850,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shirakii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6969B96EC8C2F8E6" box="[535,656,1850,1872]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">C. shirakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21C2E66A539FF9E69E7B96EC8A1F8F9" box="[665,755,1851,1872]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E6BBAB90CCB23F8C7" authority="Mengual, 2012" authorityName="Mengual" authorityYear="2012" box="[196,369,1881,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matsumurai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6BBAB90CCB23F8C7" box="[196,369,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">C. matsumurai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21C2E66A539FF9E6A04B90CCB80F8C7" box="[378,466,1881,1902]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E6AA5B90CC8A4F8C7" box="[475,758,1881,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumipenne">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6AA5B90CC8A4F8C7" box="[475,758,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Citrogramma fumipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is retained for the original male studied by Matsumura, labelled â€˜Formosa, Matsumuraâ€™, â€˜Xanth. fumipenne, 
<typeStatus id="54E0F1ADA539FF9E68CEBF56C9B5FEB1" box="[944,999,259,280]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Type</typeStatus>
Matsumuraâ€™. This male has a third round label â€˜Typeâ€™ that is the same as what Shiraki used for his 
<typeStatus id="54E0F1ADA539FF9E68CDBF14C9A1FEFF" box="[947,1011,321,342]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">types</typeStatus>
. The other two species are based on material identified by Shiraki as 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E6FD8BF0ACF6EFEDD" box="[1190,1340,351,372]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumipenne">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6FD8BF0ACF6EFEDD" box="[1190,1340,351,372]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">X. fumipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E6E35BF0AC9BEFE3B" authority="Mengual, 2012" authorityName="Mengual" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shirakii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6E35BF0AC9BEFE3B" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Citrogramma shirakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21C2E66A539FF9E6884BF2BCE07FE3A" box="[1018,1109,382,403]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is based on a male from Karenko with very large genitalia, distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E6858BFEEC9EFFE79" box="[806,957,443,464]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumipenne">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6858BFEEC9EFFE79" box="[806,957,443,464]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">C. fumipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and anepisternum anteriorly black. In his redescription of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E6F71BF8FCF59FE46" authority=", Shiraki" authorityName="Shiraki" box="[1039,1291,473,495]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumipenne">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6F71BF8FCEF7FE47" box="[1039,1189,473,495]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">X. fumipenne</emphasis>
, Shiraki
</taxonomicName>
mentioned that the male had â€˜hypopygium relatively very large, prominent, rounded... with extremely long hairsâ€™, but these genitalia characters correspond to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E6858BC01CE5FFDC3" authority="Mengual" authorityName="Mengual" authorityYear="2012" box="[806,1037,596,618]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shirakii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6858BC01C9CDFDC0" box="[806,927,596,617]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">C. shirakii</emphasis>
Mengual
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21C2E66A539FF9E6F69BC01CE3DFDC0" box="[1047,1135,596,617]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA539FF9E6841BC27C92CFB9C" blockId="44.[806,1422,198,1443]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">
The female from Taikan that 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA32FEA539FF9E6FD6BC27CFDFFD21" author="Shiraki T" box="[1192,1421,626,648]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" refId="ref56243" refString="Shiraki T. 1930. Die Syrphiden des Japanischen Kaiserreiches mit Berucksichtigung benachbarter Gebiete. Memoirs of the Faculty of Science and Agriculture Taihoku Imperial University 1." type="journal volume" year="1930">Shiraki (1930: 409)</bibRefCitation>
described as 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E68C6BCC4CE1CFD0F" box="[952,1102,657,678]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumipenne">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E68C6BCC4CE1CFD0F" box="[952,1102,657,678]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">C. fumipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a different taxon, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E6E47BCC4C9A0FD6C" authority="Mengual" authorityName="Mengual" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matsumurai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6E47BCC4C9D4FD6C" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">C. matsumurai</emphasis>
Mengual
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21C2E66A539FF9E6884BCE5CE1DFD6C" box="[1018,1103,688,709]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
It also has the round â€˜Typeâ€™ label he used for 
<typeStatus id="54E0F1ADA539FF9E688BBC9BCE74FD4A" box="[1013,1062,718,739]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">type</typeStatus>
material. This female is quite different from the male, with a lateral broad yellow vitta on scutum and anepimeron entirely yellow, but this sexual dimorphism has been seen in other species, such as 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E68A1BD1CCE38FCF4" baseAuthorityName="de Meijere" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[991,1130,840,862]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteifrons">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E68A1BD1CCE38FCF4" box="[991,1130,840,862]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">C. luteifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The size of the specimen was also indicative (the female is larger than the male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E68FABDD3CE49FC32" box="[900,1051,902,923]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumipenne">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E68FABDD3CE49FC32" box="[900,1051,902,923]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">C. fumipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), but this was not conclusive to separate them as two different taxa. Finally, when another male from 
<collectingCountry id="F34C0F9FA539FF9E6F6EBD96CE36FC70" box="[1040,1124,963,985]" name="Taiwan" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
(deposited at MCZ) was studied, I realised that this new male and the female identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E68C1BA55CE07FBBC" box="[959,1109,1024,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumipenne">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E68C1BA55CE07FBBC" box="[959,1109,1024,1045]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">C. fumipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Shiraki were the same species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA539FF9E6841BA6BC986FB39" blockId="44.[806,1422,198,1443]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">
To clarify the morphology of this species, a re-description based on the 
<typeStatus id="54E0F1ADA539FF9E6F17BA09CE98FBDB" box="[1129,1226,1116,1138]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">holotype</typeStatus>
male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E6E4EBA09C93AFB39" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumipenne">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6E4EBA09C93AFB39" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">C. fumipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is given.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA539FF9E6841BACCC996FA0A" blockId="44.[806,1422,198,1443]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">
<typeStatus id="54E0F1ADA539FF9E6841BACCC9F7FB06" box="[831,933,1177,1199]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Holotype</typeStatus>
male deposited in the National Institute of Agro-Environmental Sciences (Tsukuba, 
<collectingRegion id="499F81EDA539FF9E6858BA83C92FFB45" box="[806,893,1238,1260]" country="Japan" name="Ibaraki" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Ibaraki</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F34C0F9FA539FF9E68F1BA82C987FB45" box="[911,981,1239,1260]" name="Japan" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Japan</collectingCountry>
) and labelled: â€˜Formosa/Matsumuraâ€™ â€˜ 
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6855BAA0C923FAA3" box="[811,881,1269,1290]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">Xanth</emphasis>
./ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E6801BAA0C9A4FAA3" box="[895,1014,1269,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumipenne">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6801BAA0C9A4FAA3" box="[895,1014,1269,1290]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">fumipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/Type/Matsumuraâ€™ [first and second lines handwritten; third and fourth lines in the back of the label] â€˜Typeâ€™ [handwritten in red by Shiraki] â€˜ 
<typeStatus id="54E0F1ADA539FF9E68DABB04CE61FACF" box="[932,1075,1361,1382]" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
/ 
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6F45BB04CF09FACF" box="[1083,1371,1361,1382]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E6F45BB04CE80FACF" box="[1083,1234,1361,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Citrogramma</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA539FF9E6FA1BB04CF09FACF" box="[1247,1371,1361,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumipenne">fumipenne</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
/det. X. Mengual 20 
<emphasis id="B92F931DA539FF9E6897BB3ACE56FA2D" box="[1001,1028,1391,1412]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="143">09</emphasis>
â€™ [red, second and third lines handwritten].
</paragraph>
